      {
        "id": 6,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 7,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Climax",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Beginning of Act 3:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The Climax and the darkest moment for the Protagonist, which sets up the Resolution. Being a children's book, the darkest moment is relative."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Create a relatable and age-appropriate darkest moment for the Protagonist."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "How has the Protagonist lost hope? What is their false belief?"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Bring the Protagonist to, or just past, the point of giving up."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Amala wants to cry. With the sun now shining brightly outside, Amala apologizes to Carolina for not being able to find her boots. She is resigned to being punished for losing the boots, as the friends give up hope on playing in the puddles outside. They begin to walk back to Amala's bedroom and stop partway, deciding to go downstairs to play in the basement instead."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 3 makes up the final 25% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Climax occurs around the 75% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
