      {
        "id": 5,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 6,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Solution 3",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "End of Act 2:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The third attempt at the solution is unsuccessful as well. The Protagonist was certain that their third attempt would work, and is deeply disappointed when they have to head back to the drawing board, as a solution seems out of reach."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Identify a \"foolproof\" solution to the problem and have it fail as well."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Show the Protagonist running out of ideas and losing faith."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Don't forget the problems, solutions, and reactions must be relatable and within the range of a child."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "As they clean the room again, Carolina suggests that Amala stop and close her eyes, think about when she last had them, and then mentally retrace her steps. It's a technique Carolina's father taught her, and it works for her almost every time. Amala does that and remembers she saw her boots the previous day by the backdoor, close to the basement steps. The girls run to the backdoor to get the boots and once more see that they are not there. "
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 2 makes up 50% of the story from 25% - 75%."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Solution 3 occurs around the 55% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
