      {
        "id": 4,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 5,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Solution 2",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Middle of Act 2:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "With each attempted solution, the stakes continue to rise. But keep in mind that this is a book for children – the stakes generally will not include the fate of the world. "
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Make the stakes relatable and age-appropriate (e.g. not finishing the homework assignment, not finding a lost toy, or still not being able to reach the cookie jar)."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Consider what the Protagonist has learned from Solution 1 and create another attempt that builds on it and teaches a new lesson, without being too obvious or preachy."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Male this solution a bit more complicated while ultimately making the situation worse."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "How is the Protagonist reacting to each attempt and failure?"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Remembering that Amala's mom and dad get upset when she leaves her stuff lying around, she thinks maybe her mom put her boots in her bedroom closet. They return to Amala's room, open the closet, and find it is a mess. The girls pull everything out of the closet, but the boots are not there – and time is slipping by as they have to put everything back."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 2 makes up 50% of the story from 25% - 75%."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Solution 2 occurs around the 40% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
