      {
        "id": 3,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 4,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Solution 1",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Beginning of Act 2:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Whether on their own or with the help of friends, the Protagonist considers the problem facing them and thinks of a possible solution. Unfortunately, this first solution does not work. In children's books, the Rule of Three applies: the Protagonist should attempt and fail three times before succeeding in finding a solution."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Think about the problem from a child's point of view and how they would approach a solution."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Don't be afraid of silly solutions – remember that children do not have the same level of understanding, world perspective, or life experience as adults."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "The first attempt at a solution can be simple or obvious, leading to increasingly more sophisticated attempts."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Remember that while initial attempts are doomed to fail, they should bring the Protagonist closer to the solution with lessons learned."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "After the initial shock of discovering the boots missing, Amala runs out to the front porch with Carolina to see if she left them there to dry after the last rain. They look around everywhere, but the boots are nowhere to be seen."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 2 makes up 50% of the story from 25% - 75%."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Solution 1 occurs around the 25% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "tags": [],
        "characters": [],
