      {
        "id": 2,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 3,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Problem",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "End of Act 1:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "After the Protagonist's introduction, introduce the reader to the Central Problem that needs to be solved. There are limited pages in a children's book, so be sure to reveal the problem early."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Make the Central Problem age-appropriate and relatable to the reader (e.g. needing to finish difficult homework, wanting an expensive toy, dealing with a school bully)."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Create a Central Problem that can be easily identified by the reader."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Identify what's a stake if the problem isn't solved."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The rain stops, and the girls run to the front closet to get their boots – only to find Amala's new boots missing! Amala knows she'll be in trouble if her parents discover she's lost the boots, and they only have a short period of time to play before Carolina has to go home."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 1 makes up the first 25% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Problem should take your story from approximately 12% to the 25% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
