      {
        "id": 1,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 2,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Introduction",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Beginning of Act 1:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The opening of the story hooks the reader and introduces the Protagonist, who is usually a child or an animal. If possible, have the story start in a state of action, grappling with something that will turn into the story's main conflict. Children's books are often short and don't require a significant amount of exposition. "
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Create a Protagonist who is age appropriate and relatable, with a compelling personality and motivation."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Start the story in the midst of action."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Briefly show the Protagonist in their Ordinary World. "
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Amala is playing with an old set of toys in her bedroom with her friend Carolina as it rains outside. They are bored and biding their time until the rain stops so they can go outside and play in the puddles."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 1 makes up the first 25% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Introduction should take approximately 12% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
